channel.title: Is this normal?
channel.description: I randomly will get these headache type pains in random spots on my head, 1 at a time. They are in one central point and pulse out, then i don't feel it at all until another throb which is usually 20-30 seconds later. I went to the doctor in 8th grade and had an MRI scan done on my head and they said nothing was wrong and its just a type of headache? Does it sound right? Its not a normal headache type feeling, sometimes it will catch m.. And it just did it now, it makes my neck muscles tense up, makes the inside of my throat tingle and if it comes unexpectedly i will jolt forward (No, it is not tourettes). Right now its in the dead center back of my head, and i know it cant be because of a hit because it changes locations.
